    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  SARS-CoV-2 is a novel coronavirus that mainly affects the upper airways. Approximately one third of all detected cases is asymptomatic. We report an asymptomatic individual who tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 over a period of nine months. Of this individual, whole mouth saliva was tested by a novel fluorescence\n                  <jats:italic>in situ</jats:italic>\n                  hybridization-based assay which detects only the \u2018active\u2019 form of the virus. During the observation period of nine months, there was a possible co-infection with a second SARS-CoV-2 variant accompanied by none or very low antibody production until the possible co-infection. We suspect that the SARS-CoV-2 infection in this individual is limited to the salivary glands and does not spread (much) throughout the systemic compartment(s) of the body.\n                </jats:p>",
